[[File:Mio-jinja (Takashima) torii.JPG|thumb|220px|right|{{center|Torii}}]]'''Mizuo Shrine'' (Miojinja/Miojinja) is located in Haido, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|qid=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Takashima City|Q845794|qid=Q845794|1=Takashima, Shiga}}. {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} ({{ill|lt=Meishin Taisha|Q9610964|qid=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}}) and {{ill|lt=Modern shrine rank system|Q712534|qid=Q712534|lt=Old shrine rank|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}} is {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Prefectural shrine|1=UNKNOWN}}. {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Divine Crest|1=UNKNOWN}} is "Chrysanthemum" <ref name="Shinja Agency">[http://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=1420 Mizuo Shrine] (Shiga Prefectural Shrine Agency). </ref>.

=== Enshrined God ===
The following two deities are enshrined. </ref>.
* '''{{ill|lt=Iwakushibetsu no Mikoto|Q11587884|qid=Q11587884|1=Iwatsukiwake no Mikoto}}'''
*: The 11th {{ill|lt=Emperor Suinin|Q314850|qid=Q314850|1=Emperor Suinin}} prince. In ``Ki|Q813935}}'', he is described as the ancestor of Mio-kun (Mio clan) and Hakui-kun (Hakui clan).{{Sfn|Mizuo Shrine (Gods)|1986|p=353-355}}.
*: Deity enshrined at Kanan Shrine (south main shrine: current shrine).
* '''Himegami''
*: Refers to {{ill|lt=Shinhime|Q28415396|qid=Q28415396|1=Furihime}}, the mother of the 26th {{ill|lt=Emperor Keitai|Q349277|qid=Q349277|1=Emperor Keitai}}.
*: He is the enshrined deity of Kahoku Shrine (North Main Hall), and was transferred to Kanan Shrine in 1971|Q2475}} in 1946 ({{ill|lt=1971|Q2475|qid=Q2475|1=1971}}), where he was enshrined there.

As for the enshrined deities, there were once {{ill|lt=Sartahiko|Q3090037|qid=Q3090037|lt=Sarutahiko no Mikoto|1=Sarutahiko Ōkami}} (Kanansha), {{ill|lt=Ame no Uzume|Q462803|qid=Q462803|lt=Tencho Onna no Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Uzume}} (Kahoku There was a theory that there were two deities enshrined at the shrine, {{Sfn|Mizuo Shrine (Heibonsha)|1991}}, but the shrine is said to enshrine the ancestral deity of Mio-kun, and the two deities currently enshrined are Iwakushibetsu-no-Mikoto and Hime-kami.

